    "reasoning_content": "**Analyzing \"Cōng Cōng\"**\n\nI'm currently structuring a lesson plan for a sixth-grade class on Zhu Ziqing's \"Cōng Cōng.\" My focus is on the core theme, the lyrical techniques employed, and insightful interpretations of the beautiful passages. I'm also preparing potential discussion topics and exercises for both in-class and homework assignments. The persona I'm aiming for is that of a gentle, refined, and guiding language teacher, and I'm visualizing a visual style that includes paper textures and serif fonts.\n\n\n**Refining Lesson Aesthetics**\n\nI'm now integrating stylistic choices into the lesson's visual design, focusing on soft colors and modular presentation, using div with id response-root. I'm focusing on the core ideas of the poem, including the fleeting nature of time and the search for life's meaning, along with the lyrical devices employed, like direct/indirect expression and vivid imagery. I'm also preparing for students' contemplation of \"eight thousand days\" and the feeling of \"tears flowing.\"\n\n\n",
